Message.Title: Good riddance Icahn
Message.Msg: He can't get the money. Sure the cash flow is great, but it is a declining cash flow, but Dell and his guys can squeeze out a little value at $13.65 borrowing at low rates. If you buy at $13.40 you get $25 cents in cap gains and $8 cent in dividend = 33 cents profit. That is around a 2.4% profit less 0.1% transaction cost for holding a stock for 35 to 45 days. Annualized over 20% return.

He's better off not getting the money. I have been buying dell computers for 10 years. I ordered the fps 15 last week. It came and had software problems so they agreed to send another one out. This one also had software problems and didn't have the Office Professional software on it that I had paid for. This company is done. Sell. I'm buying a samsung computer instead. Sorry to see an American company die so fast as this one. Get your stuff together Mike.
I will say this.. I tried to buy a Microsoft surface after and they told me it cant handle microsoft word or excel...can you believe that?
Why would a company create a computer that cannot handle it's own software? Can anyone explain this?
I voted pro .25 cents profit +8 cents dividend it's not a fortune but it's a sure profit.it could be better but worse could be.
